    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Smash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> then chop it into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Tip: By bruising the cucumber the water is drawn out more easily</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>smashed cucumber</strong> and <strong>grated carrot </strong>in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and set aside</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>grated mushrooms</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until beginning to brown</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> and cook for 1 min further \u2013 these are your <strong>sweet & salty</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the mushrooms are cooking, drain any<strong> excess water</strong> from the smashed cucumber and grated carrot</p><p>Return the<strong> drained veg</strong> to the bowl and add your <strong>rice vinegar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>sweet & salty</strong> <strong>mushrooms </strong>to a bowl and return the pan (no need to wash it!) to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the pan</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>miso </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of <strong>cold water</strong> in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy miso sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Once cool, squeeze any excess water out of the spinach then combine with your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-mushroom-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cooked rice</strong> and arrange the <strong>sweet & salty</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong>,<strong> sesame spinach </strong>and <strong>quick-pickled veg </strong>on top</p><p>Top with a<strong> fried egg</strong> and a drizzle of the <strong>spicy miso sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
